The safest way to get across the border by foot from Mozambique into Zambia is walking until you reach Immigration on the plot inside a cane plantation, pack your bags in plastic or put them in a canoe, and hope for good weather in case Zambia has no more buses for the day.

The sad cliches of developing countries hold a back-firing truth – There’s “is no afternoon nap” for grown kids and grown parents here busy with daily chores and the emptiness of the mid-day slot means there’s no “after”-noon also, unless you are one of the people lucky enough to be on holiday or studying abroad or job-hunting traveling with Airbnb and the most welcoming hosts ever.

Somehow my stay for the next 3 months here in Zambia turned into a quest for finding a place to chill and rest my head. Wish me luck or help me!

Yesterday on The Border
